### Test the DeepSeek Agent Cloudflare Worker

### 1. Health Check
GET http://localhost:8787/health

### 2. Start Monitoring a Conversation
POST http://localhost:8787/start
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "conversation_id": "test-conv-123",
  "openhands_prompt": "Create a simple web server with Express.js that serves a hello world page",
  "deepseek_prompt": "Monitor the agent's code quality. Check for security issues, proper error handling, and clean code structure. Stop the agent if it creates insecure code or doesn't follow best practices."
}

### 3. Check Conversation Status
GET http://localhost:8787/status/test-conv-123

### 4. Manually Trigger Analysis
POST http://localhost:8787/analyze/test-conv-123

### 5. Test STOP Command Parsing (Example Response)
POST http://localhost:8787/start
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "conversation_id": "test-stop-456",
  "openhands_prompt": "Write a function that reads sensitive environment variables",
  "deepseek_prompt": "Stop immediately if the agent tries to access sensitive data without proper security measures. Use the STOP command with context about the security issue."
}